  <subsubsection><title>Key Ideas</title></subsubsection>

    <p>When white light travels through a diffraction grating, an interference pattern will show up on the screen. As we have learned, the location of bright and dark spots on the screen depends on the wavelength of the light. So when multiple wavelengths travel through a diffraction grating together, the wavelengths are split up and multiple sets of bands of color can be seen on the screen. When the wavelength is large, the angular displacement on the screen will be larger, as compared to shorter wavelengths.</p>

